00:53:08,266 --> 00:53:11,861
- Mika, I've been calling you for hours.
- I know, I'm in a bit of trouble.

500
00:53:12,036 --> 00:53:13,833
You miss jury service, you're in trouble.

501
00:53:14,005 --> 00:53:16,030
You're in the deepest shit
you've ever been in.

502
00:53:16,207 --> 00:53:17,970
At least I'm not down here by myself.

503
00:53:18,142 --> 00:53:20,269
Sabatin's guy from the tape?
Is he with you?

504
00:53:20,445 --> 00:53:21,935
He's on our side, Ryan.

505
00:53:22,113 --> 00:53:24,479
He wants Ozunu,
but he needs the agency's help.

506
00:53:24,849 --> 00:53:27,340
- Be careful, Mika.
- I trust him.

507
00:53:27,518 --> 00:53:31,614
<i>All right, look, I can't make any promises,</i>
<i>but if he cooperates, I'll do what I can.</i>

508
00:53:31,789 --> 00:53:33,654
- Can you meet us?
- Where?

509
00:53:34,459 --> 00:53:35,756
How about the usual?

510
00:53:43,067 --> 00:53:44,591
There he is.

511
00:53:46,738 --> 00:53:49,571
Now, it's all right. He's a good guy.

512
00:53:51,576 --> 00:53:53,237
- Mika, are you okay?
- Yeah.

513
00:53:53,411 --> 00:53:55,072
Thanks to him.

514
00:53:55,647 --> 00:53:58,115
- Why have you done this?
- Done what?

515
00:53:58,449 --> 00:53:59,814
People will die.

516
00:54:00,451 --> 00:54:02,180
- Now!
MIKA: No!

517
00:54:02,620 --> 00:54:04,281
AGENT 1:
Don't move!

518
00:54:06,524 --> 00:54:09,288
[ GRUNTING ]

519
00:54:09,460 --> 00:54:12,054
MIKA:
This is wrong! No! No!

520
00:54:12,630 --> 00:54:13,892
AGENT 2:
<i>Charlie 2, do you read me?</i>

521
00:54:15,199 --> 00:54:16,359
AGENT 3:
Move him!

522
00:54:16,768 --> 00:54:19,236
What the fuck are you doing?

523
00:54:19,570 --> 00:54:21,265
Following orders.

524
00:54:24,309 --> 00:54:26,709
- Prisoner is secure, sir.
- Right.

525
00:54:27,178 --> 00:54:29,476
AGENT 1: Sure doesn't look like
a killing machine to me, sir.

526
00:54:30,281 --> 00:54:31,908
Looks like he belongs in a boy band.

527
00:54:34,953 --> 00:54:37,421
He couldn't have heard that. Could he?

528
00:54:37,789 --> 00:54:40,656
AGENT 2: Sir?
- Ryan? This is wrong.

529
00:54:40,825 --> 00:54:42,656
I mean, it can't be legal.

530
00:54:42,827 --> 00:54:46,194
What is this place?
Your own private Guantanamo?

531
00:54:46,364 --> 00:54:50,130
It's an old GDR safe house.
Jamison wants this off the grid.

532
00:54:50,301 --> 00:54:52,895
You're making a huge mistake.

533
00:54:53,071 --> 00:54:54,732
I don't think so.

534
00:54:54,906 --> 00:54:58,603
I got reports from London, Washington
and Osaka, all tagging your boy.

535
00:54:58,776 --> 00:55:01,244
The only problem we have
is where to extradite him first.

536
00:55:01,412 --> 00:55:03,607
Two weeks ago,
there's no such thing as ninja...

537
00:55:03,781 --> 00:55:07,217
...and now every city in the world
has a warrant for one?

538
00:55:07,385 --> 00:55:09,546
- He is not the enemy.
- He's a killer, Mika.

539
00:55:09,721 --> 00:55:11,882
Weren't you telling me
it was our job to stop him?

540
00:55:12,056 --> 00:55:15,116
- You're not even listening.
- You're not saying anything worth hearing.

541
00:55:15,293 --> 00:55:18,820
Wanna do the insubordination tango?
Let's go. But not in front of the children.

542
00:55:23,101 --> 00:55:24,864
MASLOW:
Boys, get out.

543
00:55:25,169 --> 00:55:27,194
Come on, let's go!

544
00:55:28,906 --> 00:55:30,373
Damn it, I am just trying to...

545
00:55:30,541 --> 00:55:32,873
Shut up and listen to me.
We don't have much time.

546
00:55:33,044 --> 00:55:35,035
Now I don't know
what we've stumbled into...

547
00:55:35,213 --> 00:55:37,477
...but somebody's pulling
some major strings inside.

548
00:55:37,648 --> 00:55:41,948
They want him dead.
He's been fighting them for years.

549
00:55:42,487 --> 00:55:44,284
I believe you.

550
00:55:44,522 --> 00:55:47,082
I've been in this business too long
not to smell a setup...

551
00:55:47,258 --> 00:55:49,658
...but we have to be very careful
how we handle this...

552
00:55:49,827 --> 00:55:52,955
...and I cannot risk
you going AWOL on me again.

553
00:55:53,398 --> 00:55:54,763
Now, if you get into trouble...

554
00:55:56,367 --> 00:55:57,959
...you switch this on...

555
00:55:58,136 --> 00:56:01,162
...and no matter where you are,
I'll find you.

556
00:56:23,361 --> 00:56:24,487
Hey.

557
00:56:27,899 --> 00:56:29,992
You looked thirsty.

558
00:56:59,530 --> 00:57:01,657
I'm sorry,
I didn't know about any of this.

559
00:57:02,433 --> 00:57:05,061
- I know.
- You do?

560
00:57:05,503 --> 00:57:08,700
The only time you lied to me
was when you told me your size.

561
00:57:11,409 --> 00:57:13,673
How did you know that?

562
00:57:14,312 --> 00:57:17,304
Your heart. It is special.

563
00:57:23,821 --> 00:57:27,257
[ WHISPERING ] Maslow's on our side.
He's gonna try to help you.

564
00:57:27,792 --> 00:57:29,783
[ WHISPERS ]
It's too late.

565
00:57:31,329 --> 00:57:32,387
MASLOW:
No one goes here.

566
00:57:32,563 --> 00:57:34,497
MIKA:
Ryan? Ryan, can I talk to you?

567
00:57:34,665 --> 00:57:36,656
Do we have to do this again, Coretti?

568
00:57:37,602 --> 00:57:39,092
I just...

569
00:57:39,470 --> 00:57:42,303
I have reason to believe a group
of ninja may be on their way.

570
00:57:42,473 --> 00:57:46,204
I think these gentlemen can handle a few
wackjobs wearing pajamas, am I right?

571
00:57:47,044 --> 00:57:49,410
- You see?
- Yeah, but the situation we discussed...

572
00:57:49,580 --> 00:57:50,604
I'm working on that.

573
00:57:50,781 --> 00:57:52,806
- You have to give me time.
- We don't have time.

574
00:57:52,984 --> 00:57:55,976
- They're not here now, are they?
- They'll be here soon.

575
00:57:56,154 --> 00:57:57,178
How soon?

576
00:58:01,225 --> 00:58:02,249
Raizo.

577
00:58:03,161 --> 00:58:05,959
- Mika! Go with her, secure the prisoner.
AGENT 1: Go, go, go.

578
00:58:07,598 --> 00:58:09,896
AGENT 1 [ ON RADIO ]: <i>Team two, we're</i>
<i>on our way down to the holding cell.</i>

579
00:58:10,067 --> 00:58:11,056
<i>What's your 20?</i>

580
00:58:11,235 --> 00:58:13,931
AGENT 2 [ ON RADIO ]:
<i>We're just now entering section four.</i>

581
00:58:35,159 --> 00:58:36,649
AGENT 3:
Hold your fire. Hold your fire.

582
00:58:36,827 --> 00:58:38,886
- Good way to get killed.
- I need that cell open.

583
00:58:39,063 --> 00:58:41,463
- We're moving the prisoner.
- Those are not my orders.

584
00:58:41,632 --> 00:58:43,532
RAIZO: Mika! Get out of here!
- Not without you!

585
00:58:45,002 --> 00:58:46,526
Then we all die together.

586
00:59:03,221 --> 00:59:04,245
[ SPEAKS IN FOREIGN LANGUAGE ]

587
00:59:05,389 --> 00:59:07,152
AGENT 1:
Open fire! Multiple targets!

588
00:59:20,838 --> 00:59:23,033
- Open that gate.
- I can't do that.

589
00:59:23,207 --> 00:59:24,265
[ MEN SCREAMING AND GUNFIRE ]

590
00:59:24,442 --> 00:59:25,466
Go to infrared, boys.

591
00:59:26,711 --> 00:59:28,235
They're already in the room.

592
00:59:36,087 --> 00:59:37,281
AGENT 1:
Open fire!

593
00:59:38,522 --> 00:59:40,717
AGENT 2:
We're under attack! Unknown number!

594
00:59:42,159 --> 00:59:46,858
[ AGENTS SCREAMING ]

595
00:59:51,002 --> 00:59:52,469
Shit.

596
00:59:52,937 --> 00:59:56,031
[ GUNFIRE AND AGENTS
SCREAMING NEARBY ]

597
01:00:01,846 --> 01:00:03,643
Oh, Mika, Mika.

598
01:00:03,814 --> 01:00:04,803
Shh.

599
01:00:07,018 --> 01:00:08,451
I like you more and more.

600
01:00:09,720 --> 01:00:11,984
MIKA:
Okay, all right.

601
01:00:15,593 --> 01:00:16,992
Shit.

602
01:00:19,430 --> 01:00:20,624
[ AGENT SCREAMING ]

603
01:00:21,232 --> 01:00:23,826
- Mika, hurry.
- Okay.

604
01:00:26,437 --> 01:00:28,234
Mika, I don't wanna sound critical...

605
01:00:28,406 --> 01:00:30,670
Look, I'm doing the best I can here.

606
01:00:33,511 --> 01:00:36,605
- We don't have much time!
- Shit!

607
01:00:42,620 --> 01:00:43,985
Let's go.

608
01:00:59,136 --> 01:01:00,160
MIKA:
Oh, God.

609
01:01:01,639 --> 01:01:04,005
AGENT [ ON RADIO ]: <i>We are heavily engaged</i>
<i>with the enemy, I repea...</i>

610
01:01:08,746 --> 01:01:09,770
Wait here.

611
01:01:45,750 --> 01:01:47,479
Let's go.

612
01:01:51,555 --> 01:01:52,954
AGENT:
We got two men over on the side!

613
01:01:55,459 --> 01:01:57,154
MASLOW:
Get down, get down!

614
01:01:57,495 --> 01:01:59,122
Look out!

615
01:02:20,918 --> 01:02:23,148
The car's upstairs. Go.

616
01:02:24,688 --> 01:02:27,623
- Go now.
- Okay.

617
01:02:31,695 --> 01:02:33,185
NINJA 1:
Murderer.

618
01:02:33,364 --> 01:02:36,128
NINJA 2:
Traitor. So long, brother.

619
01:02:36,300 --> 01:02:41,761
NINJA 3: Vengeance, betrayal begets blood,
brother. Murderer.

620
01:02:41,939 --> 01:02:46,205
NINJA 4: Death. Kill. Murderer. Kill him.
Just. Vengeance.

621
01:02:46,377 --> 01:02:47,401
[ GRUNTS ]

622
01:02:49,380 --> 01:02:50,438
TAKESHl:
Little brother.

623
01:04:38,088 --> 01:04:39,385
[ CAR ALARM CHIRPS ]

624
01:04:55,339 --> 01:04:56,931
Come on, Raizo.

625
01:04:57,942 --> 01:05:00,502
[ GRUNTING ]

626
01:05:58,102 --> 01:06:00,093
[ SCREAMING ]

627
01:06:05,609 --> 01:06:07,668
Raizo, where are you?

628
01:06:09,146 --> 01:06:10,670
[ CAR STARTS ]

629
01:06:12,483 --> 01:06:13,711
[ GASPS ]

630
01:06:14,952 --> 01:06:16,214
Shit.

631
01:06:17,488 --> 01:06:18,978
[ THUMP ]
[ MIKA SCREAMS ]

632
01:06:19,156 --> 01:06:20,180
Ah!

633
01:06:22,426 --> 01:06:23,859
[ TIRES SCREECHING ]

634
01:06:24,928 --> 01:06:26,259
MIKA:
Fuck!

635
01:06:28,032 --> 01:06:30,466
Shit. Oh, my God. Okay.

636
01:06:33,337 --> 01:06:34,702
Okay.

637
01:06:39,443 --> 01:06:41,240
Oh, my God!

638
01:06:50,287 --> 01:06:51,618
[ MIKA SCREAMING ]

639
01:06:54,191 --> 01:06:55,818
[ CAR ALARM WAILING ]

640
01:07:21,985 --> 01:07:23,680
[ GRUNTING ]

641
01:07:35,833 --> 01:07:37,630
[ TIRES SCREECHING ]

642
01:07:45,776 --> 01:07:47,004
[ CAR HORN HONKING ]

643
01:07:48,145 --> 01:07:49,339
[ CAR HORN HONKING ]

644
01:07:52,850 --> 01:07:54,681
DRIVER 1:
Come on!

645
01:07:55,119 --> 01:07:57,246
[ HORNS HONKING ]

646
01:07:59,857 --> 01:08:01,552
DRIVER 2:
Watch it! Help!

647
01:08:10,567 --> 01:08:12,194
[ HORNS HONKING ]

648
01:08:38,796 --> 01:08:40,787
RAIZO:
Ah!

649
01:08:46,303 --> 01:08:47,565
[ HORN HONKING ]

650
01:08:50,340 --> 01:08:51,932
[ GRUNTING ]

651
01:09:00,050 --> 01:09:02,382
Goodbye, little brother.

652
01:09:04,188 --> 01:09:05,917
Get in!

653
01:09:19,436 --> 01:09:20,903
I can't believe I found you.

654
01:09:21,605 --> 01:09:23,334
I was waiting for you.

655
01:09:26,710 --> 01:09:27,972
[ GRUNTS ]

656
01:09:30,380 --> 01:09:32,075
[ RAIZO GRUNTING ]

657
01:09:32,349 --> 01:09:34,817
- Ugh!
- Oh, God.

658
01:09:35,519 --> 01:09:37,953
I have to get you to a hospital.

659
01:09:38,422 --> 01:09:40,322
No. Not a hospital.

660
01:09:41,758 --> 01:09:44,022
Just keep moving.

661
01:09:45,262 --> 01:09:46,889
[ PHONE RINGING ]

662
01:09:47,064 --> 01:09:49,760
MASLOW [ ON PHONE ]: <i>Mika, where are you?</i>
- He told me to keep moving.

663
01:09:49,933 --> 01:09:52,094
MASLOW: Is he still alive?
- <i>After a fashion.</i>

664
01:09:52,269 --> 01:09:54,829
Jesus Christ.
Listen, I'm gonna bring you in.

665
01:09:55,005 --> 01:09:57,974
- No, not this time.
- <i>There are too many people involved.</i>

666
01:09:58,141 --> 01:10:01,008
- It's just a matter of time.
- I don't think we have much time.

667
01:10:02,112 --> 01:10:03,545
Mika.

668
01:10:04,081 --> 01:10:05,105
Shit.

669
01:10:50,193 --> 01:10:52,593
I know you can't hear me...

670
01:10:53,263 --> 01:10:56,494
...so I'm sure this doesn't matter...

671
01:10:57,000 --> 01:10:59,161
...but I'm gonna say it anyway.

672
01:11:01,872 --> 01:11:04,864
I'm just a forensic researcher.

673
01:11:06,710 --> 01:11:11,113
It's like a fancy way of saying
I'm a librarian.

674
01:11:14,151 --> 01:11:16,585
By myself, I can't do anything
to help you.

675
01:11:20,624 --> 01:11:23,616
I wanted to thank you for saving my life.

676
01:11:35,639 --> 01:11:38,437
And I hope you can forgive me for this.

677
01:11:39,543 --> 01:11:41,534
- Agent Maslow! The tracking device.
MASLOW: Yeah?

678
01:11:41,712 --> 01:11:44,476
- You got a lock?
- Triangulating her position now.

679
01:11:44,881 --> 01:11:48,817
MASLOW: I want the International Task Force
mobilized and ready to go in five minutes.

680
01:12:03,600 --> 01:12:04,965
NINJA 1:
At last.

681
01:12:05,135 --> 01:12:06,602
Kill him.

682
01:12:06,770 --> 01:12:07,964
NINJA 2:
Slit his throat.

683
01:12:08,138 --> 01:12:09,298
TAKESHl:
No.

684
01:12:09,473 --> 01:12:12,772
Our father should have the honor.

685
01:12:13,577 --> 01:12:16,444
- Take him to Father.
NINJA 1: Bring him to Father.

686
01:12:16,613 --> 01:12:19,810
[ POLICE SIRENS WAILING ]

687
01:12:33,030 --> 01:12:34,861
AGENT 1: Clear.
AGENT 2: Clear.

688
01:12:38,568 --> 01:12:40,729
[ HELICOPTER WHIRRING ]

689
01:12:44,574 --> 01:12:46,838
They took him 10 minutes ago.

690
01:12:48,145 --> 01:12:49,908
He's gone.

691
01:13:17,974 --> 01:13:20,841
OZUNU:
<i>You are Ozunu.</i>

692
01:13:22,345 --> 01:13:26,714
<i>You are part of me, as I am part of you.</i>

693
01:13:27,851 --> 01:13:31,218
<i>This is the truth of your lives.</i>

694
01:13:32,722 --> 01:13:37,159
<i>And it will remain true after death.</i>

695
01:14:03,720 --> 01:14:07,281
[ DOOR OPENS AND CLOSES ]

696
01:14:16,766 --> 01:14:17,790
[ GRUNTS ]

697
01:14:25,876 --> 01:14:28,436
My child.

698
01:14:29,713 --> 01:14:32,807
It is good to see you again.

699
01:14:36,820 --> 01:14:41,154
Do you know there was a time...

700
01:14:42,392 --> 01:14:45,122
...when I looked at you...

701
01:14:45,295 --> 01:14:47,229
...I felt such pride.

702
01:14:49,566 --> 01:14:53,696
No child ever showed more promise.

703
01:14:55,505 --> 01:14:58,770
You are the son I was waiting for...

704
01:14:58,942 --> 01:15:00,910
...the one to take my place.

705
01:15:05,282 --> 01:15:10,549
And now, do you know
what you have done?

706
01:15:10,921 --> 01:15:14,982
How you have shamed my family?

707
01:15:15,325 --> 01:15:18,192
How you have hurt me?

708
01:15:22,199 --> 01:15:24,633
Why do you think I did it?

709
01:15:29,873 --> 01:15:31,602
Get this thing...

710
01:15:32,642 --> 01:15:34,007
...out of my sight.

711
01:15:34,911 --> 01:15:36,105
[ GRUNTS ]

712
01:15:45,388 --> 01:15:49,688
Tonight we avenge
our brothers and sisters.

713
01:15:51,828 --> 01:15:55,286
Tonight we avenge our honor.

714
01:15:58,101 --> 01:16:04,062
Let this death be remembered
for a thousand years.

715
01:16:14,818 --> 01:16:17,309
Weakness compels strength.

716
01:16:17,854 --> 01:16:19,754
[ RAIZO GRUNTING ]

717
01:16:22,959 --> 01:16:26,292
Betrayal begets blood.

718
01:16:26,463 --> 01:16:29,125
Ah!

719
01:16:34,070 --> 01:16:36,129
RAIZO:
You are getting weak...

720
01:16:37,107 --> 01:16:38,768
...old man.

721
01:16:39,743 --> 01:16:41,973
RAIZO:
Ah!

722
01:16:55,025 --> 01:16:56,390
[ BEEPING ]

723
01:16:56,559 --> 01:16:57,583
Father!

724
01:16:58,628 --> 01:17:01,290
[ BELL RINGING AND NINJA SHOUTING
IN JAPANESE ]

725
01:17:15,211 --> 01:17:16,337
AGENT:
Move it!

726
01:17:34,364 --> 01:17:35,388
Shit!

727
01:17:40,270 --> 01:17:43,034
- What took you?
- You knew I'd come?

728
01:17:43,840 --> 01:17:46,502
Just because I was asleep
doesn't mean I couldn't hear you.

729
01:17:46,676 --> 01:17:48,610
And I forgive you.

730
01:17:50,146 --> 01:17:51,704
Mika!

731
01:17:57,020 --> 01:17:58,544
Come, this way.

732
01:18:18,341 --> 01:18:20,138
You swore to me
you'd stay inside the APC.

733
01:18:20,310 --> 01:18:23,006
- I thought we were too late.
- First team is ready, sir!

734
01:18:23,847 --> 01:18:25,747
MASLOW: Hit it!
AGENT: Go!

735
01:18:33,323 --> 01:18:34,347
Stay here.

736
01:18:50,006 --> 01:18:51,030
AGENT:
You two, with me!

737
01:19:15,698 --> 01:19:17,563
Come, little brother.

738
01:19:17,734 --> 01:19:20,430
Let us play like old times.

739
01:19:31,347 --> 01:19:32,871
NINJA:
Ah!

740
01:19:40,190 --> 01:19:41,555
Ah!

741
01:20:02,579 --> 01:20:04,444
NINJA:
Ah!

742
01:20:07,417 --> 01:20:08,441
My turn.

743
01:20:09,219 --> 01:20:11,050
AGENT:
Watch the roof!

744
01:21:06,910 --> 01:21:08,468
Do you still think about her?

745
01:21:10,213 --> 01:21:13,148
Do you remember the sound she made
when I stuck her?

746
01:21:15,051 --> 01:21:16,109
Ah!

747
01:21:36,172 --> 01:21:37,639
